","Abt 1171":"about 1171","1172":"1172","1370":"1370","Helston, Cornwall, England":"Helston, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born in 1152, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. She married Baron Roger Antrewan about 1171, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1370, at the age of 218."},"et":{"1152–1370":"1152–1370","1146–Male":"1146–Surnud","1172–Female":"1172–Surnud","1146":"1146","1152":"1152","Abt 1171":"umbes 1171","1172":"1172","1370":"1370","Helston, Cornwall, England":"Helston, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1152–1370":"1152–1370","1146–Male":"1146–Kuollut","1172–Female":"1172–Kuollut","1146":"1146","1152":"1152","Abt 1171":"noin 1171","1172":"1172","1370":"1370","Helston, Cornwall, England":"Helston, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1152–1370":"1152–1370","1146–Male":"1146–Décédé","1172–Female":"1172–Décédée","1146":"1146","1152":"1152","Abt 1171":"environ 1171","1172":"1172","1370":"1370","Helston, Cornwall, England":"Helston, Cornouailles, Angleterre","Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Joan est née en 1152, à Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Baron Roger Antrewan environ 1171, à Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1370, à l’âge de 218 ans."},"de":{"1152–1370":"1152–1370","1146–Male":"1146–Verstorben","1172–Female":"1172–Verstorben","1146":"1146","1152":"1152","Abt 1171":"um 1171","1172":"1172","1370":"1370","Helston, Cornwall, England":"Helston, Cornwall, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Joan wurde 1152 in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat um 1171 in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom Baron Roger Antrewan geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 To